Subject: Skip the flash-attention 3 extension when hopper sources are absent

The xformers 0.0.30 sdist on PyPI omits
`third_party/flash-attention/hopper/`. `get_flash_attention3_extensions()`
does not notice: it globs that directory, ends up with `sources=[]`,
and still registers a `CUDAExtension(name="xformers._C_flashattention3",
sources=[])`. setuptools then runs the C++ linker with zero object
files and produces an empty `_C_flashattention3.so` that has no
`PyInit__C_flashattention3` symbol, so `import xformers.ops` crashes
with `ImportError: dynamic module does not define module export
function (PyInit__C_flashattention3)`.

Bail out of the function if the hopper directory is missing (sdist
build) so the extension is simply skipped. Users who build from the
git checkout — which has the submodule — keep the flash-attention 3
path.

Upstream issue: fa3 hopper sources are intentionally dropped from the
sdist. Submitting a PR upstream is tracked separately.

--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -308,6 +308,13 @@ def get_flash_attention3_extensions(cuda_version: int, extra_compile_args):
         return []

     flash_root = os.path.join(this_dir, "third_party", "flash-attention")
+    # The PyPI sdist omits third_party/flash-attention/hopper, which is where
+    # flash-attention v3's CUDA sources live. Without it we would build an
+    # empty _C_flashattention3.so that has no PyInit symbol and crashes at
+    # import time. Skip the extension entirely in that case.
+    if not os.path.isdir(os.path.join(flash_root, "hopper")):
+        return []
+
     cutlass_inc = os.path.join(flash_root, "csrc", "cutlass", "include")
     if not os.path.exists(flash_root) or not os.path.exists(cutlass_inc):
         raise RuntimeError(
